-- U.S. Futures Drop After China Raises Requirement for Bank's Reserve Ratio
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-11-19T10:35:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/u-s-futures-drop-after-china-raises-requirement-for-bank-s-reserve-ratio.html
U.S. stock-index futures dropped
after Cina raised the reserve ratio requirement for the nation’s
banks by 50 basis points from Nov. 29.  The contract on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index expiring
next month fell 0.3 percent to 1,194.00 at 10:35 a.m. in London.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
